1)Javascript is also known as client side scripting language which means data is processed from client-side. For example,if we want user to enter data and press submit
then Javascript helps in processing that data

2)It can perform actions on the website like basic calculations.

3)We can use Javascript as a client as well as server side language

4)What javascript can do in-browser:

i)Add new HTML element and control it
ii)React to events like when submit button clicked
iii)Get and set cookies for faster use

5)What javascript can't do in-browser:

i)It must be secure and must no be given low level CPU access rights.The code runs on BROWSER and NOT on our MACHINE
ii)
